PROJECT TITLE: Predicting High Risk Substance Use Among Women of Childbearing Age Using Machine Learning: Insights from the 2023 TEDS-D Dataset. 

TEAM MEMBERS: Manal Bajwa, Shekinah Edwards, Ghazalpreet Randhawa

This project was performed as part of George Mason University's HI 780: Data Mining in Health Care course taught by Dr. Abdul Hafeez in the spring 2026 semester.

The objective of this project is to predict high risk substance abuse among women of childbearing age using several data mining techniques: (1) clustering, (2) logistic regression, and (3) Random Forest.

DATASET: Treatment Episode Data Set - Discharges 2023 (TEDS-D 2023). 

DATASET LINK: https://www.samhsa.gov/data/data-we-collect/teds-treatment-episode-data-set/datafiles/teds-d-2023 

Delimted version of dataset was downloaded.

TOOLS: Google BigQuery, Weka, Python.

SECTIONS OF THIS REPOSITORY:

-Dataset Source provides a direct link to the raw dataset for download.
-Cleaning_Data.sql is the SQL file utilized in BigQuery to clean the raw dataset and formulate a cleaned dataset.
-TEDS_Project_Final.csv is the final, cleaned dataset after data preprocessing in BigQuery.
-TEDS_Project_Final.zip is the final, cleaned dataset after data preprocessing in BigQuery but in a ZIP file in case the csv file cannot be accessed.
-ModelConstructionAnd_Analysis.ipynb contains the Python notebook and code to apply the machine learning models to the dataset.


